==Old English==
===Etymology===
* (''for belly and jug'') Probably cognate with ''[[bucket]]'', and Old High German ''[[buh]]'' "belly" 
* (''for buck'') Common Germanic *''[[bukkaz]]'', whence also Old High German ''[[boc]]'', Old Norse ''[[bukkr]]''

===Noun===
'''buc''' ''m''

# [[belly]]
# [[jug]], [[pitcher]] (''probably cognate with [[bucket]]'')
# [[buck]] (''male deer'') 

